The paper deals with multi-robot path planning, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The techniques proposed involve scheduling and modifying search-space, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with coordination and optimization of multiple agents, which falls under multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper proposes techniques to improve the performance of prioritized path planning, which is a control problem, and hence falls under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses empirical evaluation to validate the proposed techniques, which is a common approach in machine learning (cs.LG).
